│ %indvars.iv = phi i64 [ poison, %if.end.i ], [ 0, %entry ]\". This indicates the increment │
│ value from the latch is poison, not an actual BinaryOperator. Immediately after, the pass  │
│ reaches canReuseFlagsFromOriginalIVInc, which tries to match both OrigInc and WideInc as   │
│ commutative binary ops anchored on their PHIs. Since WideInc is poison (or otherwise       │
│ null/incompatible), PatternMatch::match receives a null Instruction*, leading to the       │
│ dyn_cast assertion.\n\n3. Root Cause                                                       │
