│ against null or non-BinaryOperator values. In cases where expansion produces a poison      │
│ incoming value for the wide phi (e.g., non-iterating loops, unusual SCEV forms), WideInc   │
│ is not a BinaryOperator. Passing nullptr (or a non-BinaryOperator) to match triggers the   │
